<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="CCIR 601" class="currentChild" href="CCIR_601">CCIR 601</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
An international standard for digital <a title="component video" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/component_video">component video</a> devised by the <a title="Comité Consultatif International des Radiocommunications" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/Comit%C3%A9_Consultatif_International_des_Radiocommunications">Comité Consultatif International des Radiocommunications</a>. The recommendations include signal recording on the <a title="four-two-two" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/four-two-two">four-two-two</a> format, <a title="YCrCb" href="YCrCb">YCrCb</a> or <a title="RGB" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/RGB">RGB</a> color coding, and an electro/mechanical interface described by the <a title="CCIR 656" href="CCIR_656">CCIR 656</a> standard. 
</p>
